    {
      "id": "1krq52f6z",
      "questionNumber": 1,
      "questionText": "According to the valence bond theory the hybridization of central metal atom is dsp<sup>2</sup> for which one of the following compounds?",
      "options": [
        "$$NiC{l_2}.6{H_2}O$$",
        "$${K_2}[Ni{(CN)_4}]$$",
        "$$[Ni{(CO)_4}]$$",
        "$$N{a_2}[NiC{l_4}]$$"
      ],
      "correctOption": 1,
      "correctAnswer": null,
      "questionType": "MCQ",
      "marks": 4,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "subject": "Chemistry",
      "topic": "warners-theory-and-valence-bond-theory",
      "difficulty": "Easy",
      "solution": "According to VBT i.e. valence bond theory, <br><br>Electronic configuration of Ni = [Ar]3d<sup>8</sup>4s<sup>2</sup>.<br><br>(a) NiCl<sub>2</sub> . 6H<sub>2</sub>O<br><br>NiCl<sub>2</sub> . 6H<sub>2</sub>O $$\\rightarrow$$ NiCl<sub>2</sub> + 6H<sub>2</sub>O<br><br>Oxidation number of Ni(x) = x + 2($$-$$1) = 0; where x, $$-$$1 and 2 are the oxidation number of Ni, oxidation number of Cl and number of Cl atoms respectively.<br><br>NiCl<sub>2</sub> $$\\Rightarrow$$ x + ($$-$$2) = 0 $$\\Rightarrow$$ x = 2<br><br>Electronic configuration of Ni<sup>2+</sup> = [Ar]3d<sup>8</sup>4s<sup>0</sup><br><br>Cl<sup>$$-$$</sup> is a weak field ligand. So, no pairing of electrons occurs.<br><br>For C.N. = 6<br><br> <img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l14ykcas/61477100-2cb6-46ea-b577-3b273b2375cb/24024930-ab6c-11ec-91ed-1b194e5e285b/file-1l14ykcat.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l14ykcas/61477100-2cb6-46ea-b577-3b273b2375cb/24024930-ab6c-11ec-91ed-1b194e5e285b/file-1l14ykcat.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"JEE Main 2021 (Online) 20th July Morning Shift Chemistry - Coordination Compounds Question 230 English Explanation 1\"><br>(b) K<sub>2</sub>[Ni(CN)<sub>4</sub>]<br><br>K<sub>2</sub>[Ni(CN)<sub>4</sub>] $$\\rightarrow$$ 2K<sup>+</sup> + [Ni(CN)<sub>4</sub>]<sup>2$$-$$</sup><br><br>x + 4($$-$$1) $$-$$ ($$-$$2) = 0; where x, 4, $$-$$1 and $$-$$2 are the oxidation number of Ni, number of CN ligands, charge on one CN and charge on complex.<br><br>[Ni(CN)<sub>4</sub>]<sup>2$$-$$</sup> $$\\Rightarrow$$ x $$-$$ 4 + 2 = 0 $$\\Rightarrow$$ x = +2<br><br>Electronic configuration of Ni<sup>2+</sup> $$\\Rightarrow$$ [Ar]3d<sup>8</sup>4s<sup>0</sup><br><br>CN<sup>$$-$$</sup> is a strong field ligand. So, pairing of electrons occur. For C.N. = 4<br><br><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l14yl6hm/f260125a-d063-4f51-8f82-65d2050e787e/3b5497a0-ab6c-11ec-91ed-1b194e5e285b/file-1l14yl6hn.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l14yl6hm/f260125a-d063-4f51-8f82-65d2050e787e/3b5497a0-ab6c-11ec-91ed-1b194e5e285b/file-1l14yl6hn.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"JEE Main 2021 (Online) 20th July Morning Shift Chemistry - Coordination Compounds Question 230 English Explanation 2\"><br>(c) Ni(CO)<sub>4</sub><br><br>CO is neutral and strong field ligand. So, pairing of electrons occur. <br><br>Oxidation number of Ni is zero<br><br>Electronic configuration of Ni = [Ar]3d<sup>10</sup>4s<sup>0</sup><br><br>For C.N. = 4<br><br><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l14yn3pv/47fdbe69-f697-481e-9662-fad010dd102f/70cf1540-ab6c-11ec-91ed-1b194e5e285b/file-1l14yn3pw.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l14yn3pv/47fdbe69-f697-481e-9662-fad010dd102f/70cf1540-ab6c-11ec-91ed-1b194e5e285b/file-1l14yn3pw.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"JEE Main 2021 (Online) 20th July Morning Shift Chemistry - Coordination Compounds Question 230 English Explanation 3\"><br>(d) Na<sub>2</sub>[NiCl<sub>4</sub>]<br><br>Na<sub>2</sub>[NiCl<sub>4</sub>] $$\\rightarrow$$ 2Na + [NiCl<sub>4</sub>]<sup>2$$-$$</sup><br><br>x + 4($$-$$1) $$-$$ ($$-$$2) = 0; where x, 4, $$-$$1 and $$-$$2 are the oxidation number of Ni, number of CN ligands, charge on one CN and charge on complex.<br><br>[NiCl<sub>4</sub>]<sup>2$$-$$</sup> $$\\Rightarrow$$ x $$-$$ 4 + 2 = 0 $$\\Rightarrow$$ x = +2<br><br>Electronic configuration of Ni<sup>2+</sup> = [Ar]3d<sup>8</sup>4s<sup>0</sup><br><br>For C.N. = 4<br><br><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l14ynxco/e5dd1f6a-fd76-4216-b373-6efbc3c33536/87b31180-ab6c-11ec-91ed-1b194e5e285b/file-1l14ynxcp.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l14ynxco/e5dd1f6a-fd76-4216-b373-6efbc3c33536/87b31180-ab6c-11ec-91ed-1b194e5e285b/file-1l14ynxcp.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"JEE Main 2021 (Online) 20th July Morning Shift Chemistry - Coordination Compounds Question 230 English Explanation 4\"><br>Hence, only K<sub>2</sub>[Ni(CN)<sub>4</sub>] has dsp<sup>2</sup> hybridization.",
      "section": "A",
      "instruction": "",
      "examSource": "jee-main"
