    {
      "id": "IbmQJ85JPADbQ2iTtIjgy2xukf3iy9ik",
      "questionNumber": 3,
      "questionText": "The d-electron configuration of [Ru(en)<sub>3</sub>\n]Cl<sub>2</sub>\n<br>and [Fe(H<sub>2</sub>O)<sub>6</sub>]Cl<sub>2</sub>\n, respectively are :",
      "options": [
        "$$t_{2g}^4e_g^2$$ and $$t_{2g}^6e_g^0$$",
        "$$t_{2g}^6e_g^0$$ and $$t_{2g}^6e_g^0$$",
        "$$t_{2g}^6e_g^0$$ and $$t_{2g}^4e_g^2$$",
        "$$t_{2g}^4e_g^2$$ and $$t_{2g}^4e_g^2$$"
      ],
      "correctOption": 2,
      "correctAnswer": null,
      "questionType": "MCQ",
      "marks": 4,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "subject": "Chemistry",
      "topic": "crystal-field-theory-cft",
      "difficulty": "Easy",
      "solution": "[Ru(en)<sub>3</sub>\n]Cl<sub>2</sub> :\n<br><br>Here CN = 6 so octahedral splitting happens.\n<br><br>'en' is strong field ligand so $$\\Delta $$<sub>0</sub> &gt; P(pairing energy). That is why pairing of electrons happens.\n<br><br>$$\\Delta $$<sub>0</sub> = Energy gap between e<sub>g</sub> and t<sub>2g</sub> orbital.\n<br><picture><source media=\"(max-width: 320px)\" srcset=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/jgy2xukhjcchtf/784e40ff-b310-482e-be4f-e3e1aeef2653/af1ed830-2760-11eb-8293-3b6cc591631c/file-jgy2xukhjcchtg-320w.jpg\"><source media=\"(max-width: 500px)\" srcset=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/jgy2xukhjcchtf/784e40ff-b310-482e-be4f-e3e1aeef2653/af1ed830-2760-11eb-8293-3b6cc591631c/file-jgy2xukhjcchtg-500w.jpg\"><source media=\"(max-width: 680px)\" srcset=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/jgy2xukhjcchtf/784e40ff-b310-482e-be4f-e3e1aeef2653/af1ed830-2760-11eb-8293-3b6cc591631c/file-jgy2xukhjcchtg-680w.jpg\"><img src=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/jgy2xukhjcchtf/784e40ff-b310-482e-be4f-e3e1aeef2653/af1ed830-2760-11eb-8293-3b6cc591631c/file-jgy2xukhjcchtg-860w.jpg\" style=\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"JEE Main 2020 (Online) 3rd September Evening Slot Chemistry - Coordination Compounds Question 257 English Explanation 1\"></picture>\n<br><br>[Fe(H<sub>2</sub>O)<sub>6</sub>]Cl<sub>2</sub> :\n<br><br>Here CN = 6 so octahedral splitting happens.\n<br><br>H<sub>2</sub>O is weak field ligand so $$\\Delta $$<sub>0</sub> &lt; P(pairing energy). That is why no pairing of electrons happens.\n<br><br>$$\\Delta $$<sub>0</sub> = Energy gap between e<sub>g</sub> and t<sub>2g</sub> orbital.\n<picture><source media=\"(max-width: 320px)\" srcset=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/jgy2xukhjcs3rb/f71dc893-7247-41ad-9487-94cc33f6d1dd/6134f170-2762-11eb-8293-3b6cc591631c/file-jgy2xukhjcs3rc-320w.jpg\"><source media=\"(max-width: 500px)\" srcset=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/jgy2xukhjcs3rb/f71dc893-7247-41ad-9487-94cc33f6d1dd/6134f170-2762-11eb-8293-3b6cc591631c/file-jgy2xukhjcs3rc-500w.jpg\"><source media=\"(max-width: 680px)\" srcset=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/jgy2xukhjcs3rb/f71dc893-7247-41ad-9487-94cc33f6d1dd/6134f170-2762-11eb-8293-3b6cc591631c/file-jgy2xukhjcs3rc-680w.jpg\"><img src=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/jgy2xukhjcs3rb/f71dc893-7247-41ad-9487-94cc33f6d1dd/6134f170-2762-11eb-8293-3b6cc591631c/file-jgy2xukhjcs3rc-860w.jpg\" style=\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"JEE Main 2020 (Online) 3rd September Evening Slot Chemistry - Coordination Compounds Question 257 English Explanation 2\"></picture>",
      "section": "A",
