    {
      "id": "1ldu3xkmx",
      "questionNumber": 7,
      "questionText": "<p>Total number of moles of AgCl precipitated on addition of excess of AgNO$$_3$$ to one mole each of the following complexes $$\\mathrm{[Co(NH_3)_4Cl_2]Cl,[Ni(H_2O)_6]Cl_2,[Pt(NH_3)_2Cl_2]}$$ and $$\\mathrm{[Pd(NH_3)_4]Cl_2}$$ is ___________.</p>",
      "options": [],
      "correctOption": 0,
      "correctAnswer": null,
      "questionType": "MCQ",
      "marks": 4,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "subject": "Chemistry",
      "topic": "warners-theory-and-valence-bond-theory",
      "difficulty": "Easy",
      "solution": "$\\left[\\mathrm{Co}\\left(\\mathrm{NH}_{3}\\right)_{4} \\mathrm{Cl}_{2}\\right] \\mathrm{Cl} \\stackrel{\\mathrm{AgNO}_{3}}{\\longrightarrow} \\mathrm{AgCl}$\n<br/><br/>\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n& {\\left[\\mathrm{Ni}\\left(\\mathrm{H}_{2} \\mathrm{O}\\right)_{6}\\right] \\mathrm{Cl}_{2} \\stackrel{\\mathrm{AgNO}_{3}}{\\longrightarrow} 2 \\mathrm{AgCl}} \\\\\\\\\n& {\\left[\\mathrm{Pd}\\left(\\mathrm{NH}_{3}\\right)_{4}\\right] \\mathrm{Cl}_{2} \\stackrel{\\mathrm{AgNO}_{3}}{\\longrightarrow} 2 \\mathrm{AgCl}}\n\\end{aligned}\n$$\n<br/><br/>\nTotal moles of $\\mathrm{AgCl}$ precipitated $=5$",
      "section": "A",
      "instruction": "",
      "examSource": "jee-main"
    },
    {
      "id": "2mJTEi4mPP0MNw9M6htvh",
      "questionNumber": 8,
      "questionText": "The following ligand is :\n<img src=\"https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/GatEaxLrxwVN9AURA/AN6yeccinqgvdjeTpcGAXXiW7LMYV/EzOGIEVmnuSP91fPIzHskF/image.png\" style=\"max-width: 100%;  height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"JEE Main 2019 (Online) 8th April Morning Slot Chemistry - Coordination Compounds Question 291 English\">",
      "options": [
        "hexadentate",
