    {
      "id": "gMdsz15sySHNjT7B",
      "questionNumber": 9,
      "questionText": "On treatment of 100 mL of 0.1 M solution of CoCl<sub>3</sub>. 6H<sub>2</sub>O with excess AgNO<sub>3</sub>; 1.2 $$\\times$$ 10<sup>22</sup> ions are precipitated. The complex is :",
      "options": [
        "[Co(H<sub>2</sub>O)<sub>3</sub>Cl<sub>3</sub>].3H<sub>2</sub>O ",
        "[Co(H<sub>2</sub>O)<sub>6</sub>]Cl<sub>3</sub>",
        "[Co(H<sub>2</sub>O)<sub>5</sub>Cl]Cl<sub>2</sub>.H<sub>2</sub>O ",
        "[Co(H<sub>2</sub>O)<sub>4</sub>Cl<sub>2</sub>]Cl.2H<sub>2</sub>O "
      ],
      "correctOption": 2,
      "correctAnswer": null,
      "questionType": "MCQ",
      "marks": 4,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "subject": "Chemistry",
      "topic": "warners-theory-and-valence-bond-theory",
      "difficulty": "Easy",
      "solution": "Moles of complex = $${{Molarity \\times Volume\\left( {mL} \\right)} \\over {1000}}$$\n<br><br>= $${{100 \\times 0.1} \\over {1000}}$$ = 0.01 mole\n<br><br>Moles of ions precipitated with excess of AgNO<sub>3</sub>\n<br><br>= $${{1.2 \\times {{10}^{22}}} \\over {6.023 \\times {{10}^{23}}}}$$ = 0.02 mole\n<br><br>So 0.01 × n = 0.02\n<br><br>$$ \\Rightarrow $$ n = 2\n<br><br>It means 2Cl<sup>–</sup> ions present in ionization sphere.\n<br><br>$$ \\therefore $$ The formula of complex is [Co(H<sub>2</sub>O)<sub>5</sub>Cl]Cl<sub>2</sub>.H<sub>2</sub>O ",
      "section": "A",
      "instruction": "",
      "examSource": "jee-main"
    },
